                            <comment id="14231871" author="rhatch" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 18:21:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to mention above that the issue seems more likely to occur when I query across several partitions than when querying across just 2 or 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14232085" author="rhatch" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2014 20:23:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue can be reliably reproduced with my (semi-experimental) dtest branch here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/tree/scenarios_with_page_limit&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/tree/scenarios_with_page_limit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;export PRINT_DEBUG=true
nosetests -vs paging_test.py:TestPagingWithModifiers.test_with_limit
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14237874" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 8 Dec 2014 13:58:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Russ, the test you attached is failing with the same error messages in 2.0-HEAD as well, so I am adding that to the reproduced versions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14252347" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2014 21:49:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The way that the total query limit for multi-partition IN queries was being determined was erroneous.  I don&apos;t really understand the previous logic in &lt;tt&gt;computeRemaining()&lt;/tt&gt;, but as a fix, the original query limit is passed through to &lt;tt&gt;MultiPartitionQueryPager&lt;/tt&gt; and used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rhatch&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rhatch&quot;&gt;rhatch&lt;/a&gt; I tested this manually with a python script.  Do you want to expand the coverage for this type of query in your paging tests, or should I go ahead and open a PR for the dtests?  The test focus should be on multi-partition IN queries with a mixture of limits and page sizes (including no limit and paging disabled).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=slebresne&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;slebresne&quot;&gt;slebresne&lt;/a&gt; can you review?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
